Currently, the documentation for the *[Create Customer Request|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-servicedesk/REST/latest/#servicedeskapi/request-createCustomerRequest]* action states that "Adding attachments via this method is currently not supported."

Attachments (specially image attachments) are a big part of customer requests / issues so the lack of ability to upload them to a customer request is, IMO, a big limitation that, at first sight, does not seem that complex/hard to fix.

An alternative would be to expose a
{noformat}
servicedeskapi/request/{issueIdOrKey}/attachment
{noformat}
resource that would support adding (and later getting) attachments to(/of) an existing request/issue.

Ideally, both would be needed, but either one would be enough to at least partially fix the problem.

I know the standard Jira REST API supports attachments, but that is outside the scope of the Jira Service Desk REST API and is not really a solution.

Thanks for the great work so far!

I did not find any relevant existing issue to track progress on this current limitation, so I have created this one.

