h3. Summary
Request Type is not created via API when it is associated to Epic.

h3. Environment
Service Desk

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Find out the Epic IssueType ID;
# Run the command below to create it:
{code}
curl -X POST -H 'X-ExperimentalApi: opt-in'  -i  'https://UUU:PPP@HHH.atlassian.net/rest/servicedeskapi/servicedesk/55/requesttype'  -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '\{
    "issueTypeId": {Epic IssueType ID},
    "name": "IT Test",
    "description": "Get IT Help",
    "helpText": "xxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
}'
{code}
# Run to check:
{code}
curl  -H 'X-ExperimentalApi: opt-in'  -i  'https://UUU:PPP@HHH.atlassian.net/rest/servicedeskapi/servicedesk/55/requesttype/251/field'
{code}

h3. Expected Results
Create the Request Type.

h3. Actual Results
{code}
\{"errorMessage":"The request type you are trying to view does not exist.","i18nErrorMessage":\{"i18nKey":"sd.customerview.error.requestTypeNotFound","parameters":[]}}
{code}

h3. Notes
The request type is being created in the DB but it is not being displayed and accessible.

h3.Workaround
Use a different Issue Type from Epic and use on that is being used in the project.

